Release Notes
Performance & Strategy Testing Notes
This strategy employs computationally intensive algorithms, most notably the Lorentzian KNN classifier, which executes a distance calculation loop (up to 50 iterations per bar) involving logarithmic operations across four normalized feature dimensions. Combined with four request.security() calls for multi-timeframe analysis, Smart Money Concepts array processing (demand/supply zone tracking with reverse iteration), and a 20-bar volume pressure loop, the cumulative computational load is substantial.
As a result, the strategy tester may not display results on all instruments or timeframes. Pine Script enforces a runtime limit (~40 seconds), and on charts with a large number of bars (10,000+), the calculation budget may be exhausted before completion. This is expected behavior for a strategy of this complexity, not a bug.

Tips for Best Results

If the strategy tester shows no results, try reducing the Training Window (KNN lookback) to 30 or switching to a higher timeframe.
Use the Confluence Score in the dashboard as a guide — scores of 4.0+ out of 5.55 indicate the strongest setups.
This strategy is designed as an analytical framework and signal confirmation tool, not a standalone automated trading system. Always combine with proper risk management and your own market analysis.
